"{\n    \"Title\": \"Notes to Consolidated Financial StatementsMarch 31, 2020\",\n    \"row 1\": \"2. Basis of presentation and significant accounting policies, continued:\",\n    \"row 2\": \"(b) Basis of accounting:\",\n    \"row 3\": \"Revenues and expenditures are reported using the accrual basis of accounting. Revenues\",\n    \"row 4\": \"are recognized as they are earned and measurable. Expenditures are recognized as they\",\n    \"row 5\": \"are incurred and measurable as a result of receipt of goods or services and the creation of\",\n    \"row 6\": \"a legal obligation to pay.\",\n    \"row 7\": \"(c) Cash:\",\n    \"row 8\": \"Cash and cash equivalents consist of unrestricted cash on hand and balances held by\",\n    \"row 9\": \"major financial institutions.\",\n    \"row 10\": \"(d) Short-term investments:\",\n    \"row 11\": \"Short-term investments are recorded at the lower of cost and fair market value. The\",\n    \"row 12\": \"investments are held for short-term unspecified purposes and are generally comprised of\",\n    \"row 13\": \"monthly interest paying investment accounts, term deposits and guaranteed investment\",\n    \"row 14\": \"certificates with major financial institutions, and have maturities within one year.\",\n    \"row 15\": \"(e) Tangible capital assets:\",\n    \"row 16\": \"Tangible capital assets are recorded at cost. The First Nation provides for amortization\",\n    \"row 17\": \"using the straight-line method designed to amortize the cost, less any residual value, of\",\n    \"row 18\": \"the tangible capital asset over the estimated useful life of the asset. The annual\",\n    \"row 19\": \"amortization rates are as follows:\",\n    \"row 20\": \"Asset Basis Rate\",\n    \"row 21\": \"Buildings and building additions straight-line 10-40 years\",\n    \"row 22\": \". Water and electrical systems straight-line 10 & 50 years\",\n    \"row 23\": \"Roads straight-line 10-40 years\",\n    \"row 24\": \"Vehicles straight-line 3-10 years\",\n    \"row 25\": \"Furniture, equipment and other straight-line 1-10 years\",\n    \"row 26\": \"Computer hardware and software straight-line 2-5 years\",\n    \"row 27\": \"Infrastructure projects straight-line 10 years\"\n}"